radiographic_examinations.findings: In the background of moderate free fluid, there is a seemingly blind ended structure appearing contiguous with the cecum measuring 7 mm in maximum diameter at the focal point of patient's pain. Anteverted uterus measures 7.1 x 4.1 x 5.5 cm and is normal. Endometrial stripe measures 9 mm and is homogeneous. Ovaries are normal size with a central cyst measuring 2.2 cm suggestive of a ruptured cyst. Moderate free fluid with trace areas of debris, possibly related to ruptured right cyst.
